projects.description:
As a Delivery Pipeline Architect, Ilia is responsible for building an orchestration layer for end-to-end delivery of various client's applications. Ilia is collaborating with more than 12 DevOps teams to connect automated deployments, sanity checks, quality assurance processes across multiple environments into a all-in-one delivery solution.

Starting from July 1st, Ilia took 2nd role (Scrum Master) and was responsible for setting up and coaching on Scrum process.

Responsibilities include:
- diving into various application architectures to define pipeline requirements and dependencies;
- setting up and optimizing the Delivery Pipeline for 12 applications using Release Automation, CI tooling, Test Automation;
- coaching on and facilitating Scrum implementation;
- Scrum Master;
- supporting the team with removing impediments and aligning with other teams.

Main responsibility for Ilia implementing this role is defining product strategy and leveraging CI and CD tools and practices across client's products. 

Responsibilities include:
- aligning with business on priorities, expectations and timelines;
- setting up the strategy for adoption of Continuous Integration & Continuous Delivery in product teams;
- defining the Configuration Management strategy and helping teams adopt strong configuration management and version control practices;
- aligning on release and test automation knowledge transfers;
- improving communication and collaboration between CICD and product DevOps teams.

